
Main Answer:
BitPay applies automated fraud prevention measures when processing personal data to comply with legal obligations, including financial services regulations like the Bank Secrecy Act and anti-money laundering laws.

Key Points:
• BitPay is considered a controller for personal data processing as outlined in the Privacy Notice.
• They may share Shopper data with Merchants in cases of suspected fraud or ongoing investigations.
• The company is primarily located in the US, and some data transfers outside the EEA are necessary for providing services.
• BitPay encourages users to contact their Data Protection Officer for any questions or concerns regarding data protection.

GDPR References:
Article 6(1)(c) - Lawfulness of Processing
Article 44 - General Principle for Transfers